<p>The following methodologies are used for threats classification during the assessment:</p>
<ul>
<li><p><em><b>Microsoft STRIDE</b> Methodology is used to identify threats relevant to the application. STRIDE was developed to educate developers on how to think about computer security threats.&nbsp;</em>
<strong>For a detailed description of STRIDE threats please visit&nbsp;<a class="createlink" href="https://www.microsoft.com/security/blog/2007/09/11/stride-chart/">Microsoft STRIDE</a>&nbsp;page.</strong></p>
</li>
<li><p><em>The <b>OWASP Top 10</b> is a standard awareness methodology for developers and web application security. It represents a broad consensus about the most critical security risks to web applications.&nbsp;</em>
<strong>For the addition information please see&nbsp;<a class="createlink" href="https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/">OWASP Top Ten</a>.&nbsp;</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
